      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRINKA BRETT (2) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 0.8 lengths from the winner Bell Mac Magic in second(22.85) at Dubbo. The form out of his last race has been franked. Makes plenty of appeal. SLICK CHANCE (7) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 18.62 beating Lone Dazzler. Draws out wide but goes well over this trip. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. KILLER FORGE (1) did a good job to finish third last time out over 330m at this track (19.28) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot. Can turn it around this time. DANA MAC (3) scored with plenty to spare last time. Hard to beat again.",
